# AIRGÉ — brand copy and constants

## Single source of truth

- **`src/constants/index.js`**: `brandName`, `navLinks`, hero/problem/solution/impact/pricing/faq/cta/footer, `appCtaHref`, `whatsappCtaHref`.
- Sections in `src/sections/*` should **import** copy from constants, not duplicate long strings.
- Nav: `src/components/Nav.jsx` + `src/components/NavBrand.jsx` (text mark **AIRGÉ**, `text-gradient`).

## Centralize in constants

- Headlines, intros, bullet lists, FAQ items, pricing offer, CTA labels/hrefs.
- Footer columns, social links, support contact when shown.

## Hardcoding

- OK only for short, presentational strings unlikely to change.
- Never hardcode **LivSight**, delivery/logistics copy, or old domains on the home page.

## Legacy cleanup (when touching branding)

Search and replace or update:

- `LivSight`, `livsight`, `lifsight.com`, `lifsight.com`
- WhatsApp-first CTAs where the product CTA should be `appCtaHref`
- `src/components/SEO.jsx` (`siteName`, `baseUrl`), `index.html`, `package.json` name if still template-branded

In summaries for branding work, include a brief **Leftovers check**: terms searched, files touched, any intentional exceptions.
